setup environment

- install arduino ide
- file -> reference-> setting tab -> additional board manager urls: http://arduino.esp8266.com/stable/package_esp8266com_index.json-->ok
- tools -> manager board -> enter esp8266 or 8266 -> install

- install git

- install vscode
- install PlatformIO for vscode
- open home PlatformIO
    - select boards -> search esp8266 -> install


- clone project
- add project to vscode
- open folder .vscode, open c_cpp_properties.json to add path of package or library be missing

